To build better AI strategy prompts, treat them like decision frameworks. First, give clear context about where your business is right now and what you’re trying to achieve. Then tell the AI what kind of analysis you need.

Always include your limits and how you’ll measure success. Ask for a few different options, not just one answer. That way you can compare. (1/2)

external.description:
While everyone has been obsessing over AI chatbots, a silent revolution has been happening in the physical world. The code has been given a body. This is the story of the new global arms race: the battle for the world's first true humanoid robot.

In this episode, we expose how Generative AI and LLMs have lit a fire under the robotics industry, transforming clunky machines into adaptable, intelligent beings. But this revolution is being fought on two fronts. In one corner, you have the American titans—Figure AI, Tesla, and Boston Dynamics—locked in a battle for supreme intelligence and quality. In the other, you have China's state-subsidized manufacturing might, aiming to flood the world with low-cost humanoids at an unprecedented scale.

We're putting the robots head-to-head: the sophisticated Figure 02, the ambitious Tesla Optimus, the legendary Boston Dynamics Atlas, and China's acrobatic Unitree G1. Is your next co-worker, or even your next butler, being built right now in a lab in Austin or a factory in Shenzhen?

This isn't just about cool tech; it's a clash of ideologies and a race that will define the future of work and humanity itself.

Hit play to witness the dawn of the robot age. After you listen, tell us in the comments: which strategy do you think will win—America's brain or China's brawn?
external.title: While You Were Arguing With ChatGPT, They Gave It a Body.

external.description:
What if the line between science and magic was so thin, a man could simply... step across it and disappear forever?

In 1994, the brilliant neuroscientist Dr. Jacobo Grinberg vanished without a trace. This wasn't just any scientist. Grinberg was on the verge of proving a theory so profound it would rewrite reality itself: his Syntergic Theory, which posited that our world is an informational matrix—a simulation—that can be altered by human consciousness.

This isn't just another unsolved mystery; it's a rabbit hole where quantum physics meets ancient magic. We'll follow Grinberg's journey from his groundbreaking brain research to his encounters with the powerful shaman Dona Pachita, a woman who could perform spiritual surgeries with her bare hands and who claimed to know the secrets of the matrix before she, too, vanished.

So, what happened to Jacobo Grinberg? Was he silenced by the CIA for getting too close to their psychic Stargate Project? Was it a simple case of foul play involving his suspicious wife? Or did he achieve the impossible? Did he learn the final secret from Pachita and do what so many dream of... and finally "leave the Matrix"?

You be the judge. Hit play and join us down the rabbit hole. Let us know your theory in the comments—foul play, a government conspiracy, or did he find the exit?
